$ Microsoft Teams

{ Team

  A *team* is a collection of people, content, and tools.

  A team is either
    • private (accessible to invited people only)
    • public

  Members in a team are either
    • team owners
    • team members

}
{ Channel

  Within a team, *channels* are used as communication channels. Each channel focus on a particular topic.

  Channels can be extended with *apps*. Types(?) of apps seem to be tabs, connectors and bots.

  As with teams, channels can be private or open.

}
